Review saved. Here's a summary of the findings for `nsqd/channel.go`:

**8 findings total** (6 BUG, 2 QUESTION) — Assessment: **FIX FIRST**

| # | Type | Severity | Line(s) | Description |
|---|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| 1 | BUG | High | 571-572, 601-602 | `goto exit` in `processInFlightQueue`/`processDeferredQueue` aborts all remaining timeout processing when a single concurrent FIN/TOUCH races with PeekAndShift. Should `continue`, not `goto exit`. |
| 2 | BUG | Medium | 574, 611 | `put(msg)` return value ignored in both queue processors — messages silently lost on backend write failure. |
| 3 | BUG | Medium | 320-323 | `PutMessageDeferred` lacks `exitMutex`/`Exiting()` guard, unlike `PutMessage` — can add deferred messages to an exiting channel. |
| 4 | BUG | Medium | 401-417 | `AddClient` TOCTOU race: count check under RLock, insert under separate Lock — `MaxChannelConsumers` can be exceeded. |
| 5 | BUG | Medium | 441 | `RemoveClient` reads `len(c.clients)` after releasing write lock — data race can prevent ephemeral channel cleanup. |
| 6 | BUG | Low | 215 | `flush()` reads map lengths without locks (race detector violation, log-only impact). |
| 7 | QUESTION | Medium | 182-183 | Can `processInFlightQueue` race with `exit()` after passing the `Exiting()` check? |
| 8 | QUESTION | Low | 306-316 | Ordering guarantee for MemQueueSize==0 depends on diskqueue FIFO under concurrent writes. |
